"{\"content\":{\"body\":\"BNB is widely used in the Binance ecosystem and other environments, so users can flexibly decide how to use BNB in ​​their hands. For example, you can use BNB to pay for travel, purchase virtual gifts, and more. According to our estimates, millions of BNB have been used by users to pay for travel expenses, purchase goods, borrow money, rewards, create smart contracts and other transactions.\\nIn addition, many people use BNB to pay transaction fees. In the trading platform alone, 2 million users used BNB to pay transaction fees for more than 127 billion transactions, totaling more than 40 million BNB. Let's take a look at how to pay transaction fees through BNB.\\n\\nWhen trading digital currencies on the Binance trading platform, a standard handling fee of 0.1% will be charged for each transaction (the transaction fee depends on the monthly trading volume and BNB holdings). Traders can use the assets being traded or BNB to pay transaction fees. You can also enjoy special discounts when you choose to pay with BNB.\\nTherefore, if you conduct large-scale transactions on Binance, you should consider obtaining BNB and using it to pay fees. Please note that the deduction of transaction fees follows a specific fee schedule. Therefore, you must check the current spot transaction fee schedule. It is also worth noting that the fee schedule followed by the Binance Contracts platform is slightly different.\",\"timestamp\":1636028835,\"title\":\"What are the uses of Binance Coin?\"},\"digest\":\"Z8Zpe47HdK7HbIURYpFhhArjtNq2aUveSi9FBrWtsKE\",\"authorship\":{\"contributor\":\"0x024A49cB8a320a9Add27bDfBbF385cD1aAb6Ea04\",\"signingKey\":\"{\\\"crv\\\":\\\"P-256\\\",\\\"ext\\\":true,\\\"key_ops\\\":[\\\"verify\\\"],\\\"kty\\\":\\\"EC\\\",\\\"x\\\":\\\"IvFQAbc0Lk8t97-a9q0WQR0OLNH8VGx9WCMuS2XlmzI\\\",\\\"y\\\":\\\"8dqD6_8r5Zp7CBhu2kOh3NZRcB1zOJTdbS_EJG9f8AU\\\"}\",\"signature\":\"_M8rxZkMxQtKAcN9xaxp0m9PzbSMNh4BvRLbaOwBP5s8_pKERV_XUGx7PvtZv_16Yl6E_JlwHHg9dRZ